subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks. This species is transferred from
Aloconota Thomson, 1858
to
Earota
based on Gusarov’s diagnosis of the latter genus (2002). It corresponds to
Earota
and differs from
Aloconota
in the following characters: large and broad body (small and narrow body in
Aloconota
); antennomere 11 distinctly longer than preceding two combined (antennomere 11 about as long as preceding two combined in
Aloconota
); infraorbital carina complete (infraorbital carina incomplete in
Aloconota
); mesocoxae moderately separated (mesocoxae narrowly separated in
Aloconota
); mesoventral process slightly pointed at apex (mesoventral process distinctly pointed at apex in
Aloconota
); metatarsomere 1 about as long as 2 (metatarsomere 1 longer than 2 in
Aloconota
); empodial seta shorter than claw (empodial seta longer than claw in
Aloconota
).
